<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 07 at 12:25PM MDT  by NWS Aberdeen</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHEASTERN HUGHES AND
NORTHEASTERN LYMAN COUNTIES THROUGH 200 PM CDT...
At 124 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Byre Lake, or 11 miles southwest of Lower Brule, moving northeast at
25 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Lower Brule, Medicine Butte, Counselor Creek Boat Access Area, Lake
Sharpe, Lower Brule Reservation, and Crow Creek Reservation.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
